## 3. Data Understanding

### 3.1 Data Source
**Primary:** [YouTube Comments Sentiment Dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/amaanpoonawala/youtube-comments-sentiment-dataset) (1M+ comments with labels)

**Alternative:** Collect custom data using YouTube Data API v3

### 3.2 Data Description
- **Size:** ~1,000,000 comments
- **Features:** comment text, video ID, likes, timestamp
- **Target:** Sentiment labels (positive, negative, neutral)
- **Format:** CSV

### 3.3 Data Quality Considerations
- **Spam comments:** Need filtering
- **Class imbalance:** May need SMOTE or class weights
- **Emojis:** Require special handling
- **Slang/abbreviations:** Need normalization
- **Multiple languages:** Filter to English only

### 3.4 Exploratory Questions
- What is the distribution of sentiment labels?
- What is the average comment length?
- How many comments contain emojis?
- Are there spam patterns?
- Is there correlation between likes and sentiment?

